http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/3-held-logs-worth-Rs.-15-lakh-seized/article13980630.ece

The forest officials of Puttur range on Saturday midnight nabbed three red sanders smugglers and seized an SUV carrying red sanders logs worth over Rs. 15 lakh during regular patrolling in Puttur town.Forest Range Officer (Puttur) M. Reddappa said that the beat party that was on their job on the Tirupati-Chennai national highway, intercepted an SUV and seized logs were seized, and nabbed three inmates, two from Chennai and one from Pichatur in Chittoor district. He said that the vehicle was on its way to Chennai after collecting the contraband at the foot of Tirumala hills.